flowRoot.flowPara: (A) Capture and reverse transcription of mRNA molecules with barcoded beads (top) can lead to the production of different cDNA species (bottom). The expected product should contain Illumina adapter P5, indexed adapter N70X, Template Switch Oligo (TSO) sequence, mRNA, polyT, optical sequencing primer sequence (OP1), and the bead-side primer handle composed of SMART primer sequence + AC dinucleotide (green, rounded box). Longread analysis revealed byproducts lacking parts of the bead-associated oligonucleotides and cDNAs with TSO-sequence on both ends. (B) The spacemake longread module annotates pacbio reads against a catalog of known cDNA building blocks. It then analyzes their presence/absence and ordering to reveal common signatures (left). The dominant cDNA species in this library were TSO-terminated artifacts (center, pale green). Only ~9% of pacbio reads featured the bead-side primer handle (center, bright green, "bead-related"). Of these, just 63% also contained the expected OP1 and polyT (right, dark green), while the remainder appears incomplete. (C) Similar to (B) but for an improved sequencing library. Here, almost all reads feature the bead handle (center, bright green), of which more than 80% furthermore carry the full complement of expected additional building blocks (right, dark green).
